In his detailed analysis, Guide explains the relevance of that moment he chose.
“The collapse of the new military administration in Argentina, after the Galtieri dictatorship (1981-1982), was the decisive moment where political history was inaugurated, establishing a new political paradigm that marked the recovery of democracy and gave it the differentiation, not only chronological one, but above all, strategic and geopolitical, from the previous period. No difference in fact, applies to the following 30 years, because many structural elements clearly conditioned what would happen in that new democratic era beyond the casual coincidence whose beginning accompanied the return of the families to power.” Global Thinkers, The New Global Elite 2013 avaliaÇÕes
